snippet: A panel of judges also blessed the presidential bid of Hosni Mubarak’s last prime minister, putting Egypt’s troubled move to democracy in grave doubt.
abstract: Egypt's Supreme Constitutional Court orders the country's first democratically elected Parliament to be dissolved, escalating a struggle by remnants of the old elite to block Islamists from coming to power; if the ruling is carried out, whoever wins the presidential race would take power without the check of a sitting Parliament and could exercise significant influence over the elections to form a new one.

byline.contributor: Mayy El Sheikh and Dina Salah Amer contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: A panel of judges also blessed the presidential bid of Hosni Mubarak’s last prime minister, putting Egypt’s troubled move to democracy in grave doubt.
